Title: Beautician
Description: A beautician can be known by many titles depending on the specialization: esthetician, cosmetologist, hairstylist, and hairdresser. A beautician's responsibility is to improve the physical appearance of clients and help them to feel better about themselves.

Title: Carpenter
Description: A carpenter is responsible for working with wood to build and repair structures and other items and they also may have to select and source appropriate materials depending on project needs. Their duties include calculating quotes, meeting with clients and creating design plans for remodeling projects.

Title: Plumber
Description: Install, repair, and maintain pipes, valves, fittings, drainage systems, and fixtures in commercial and residential structures. Collaborate with general contractors, electricians, and other construction professionals. Plumbers will be highly skilled in understanding and following building plans and blueprints.

Title: Chef
Description: On demand Chefs is one of the best services we provide. Be it office, home, ceremonies, or even a picnic location, our expert chef can be there with you to cater the most delicious dishes that you have come across. The chef usually works with a team. You may decide on menu or the chef may also suggest items for the menu if requested

Title: Gardener
Description: Gardeners tend to have a passion for certain elements in gardening be it design, color patterns, textures or types of foliage, flowers or species of plants. They seem to get excited when you mention something interesting about their garden or something they personally take pride in establishing.They have a deep understanding of flora and fauna.

Title: Electrician
Description: Electricians work on electrical equipment and in homes, factories, businesses, and buildings, both existing and under construction, they install, repair, and maintain power, lighting, communications, and control systems. Electrician would have an in-depth knowledge of the home/office appliances and will provide the right service at your doorstep.

Title: Caretaker
Description: A Caretaker takes care of the security and maintenance of community buildings. Their duties include cleaning, performing simple repairs and maintenance tasks and performing security checks for the buildings in their care. In addition, the caretaker may also look after pets in the building.

Title: Nanny
Description: A great nanny shows absolute diligence and respect to the requirements of the family. They take time to understand the fine details of how the parents like things to be done and also provide thorough details on what he/she does with the children throughout their time with the children.

Title: Driver
Description: A Driver is a professional who drives clients around in an efficient, safe and timely manner. In addition to maintaining regular cleaning services for their vehicle as well as managing payments on time each week/monthly cycle goes by; drivers also plan routes based on road conditions.

Title: Bodyguard
Description: A bodyguard is a type of security guard, government law enforcement officer, or service member who protects a person or a group of people. Bodyguards are highly skilled with right combat training and are capable to work through any situation giving you confidence in daily life.

Title: Painter
Description: A Painter is a professional who helps prepare surfaces, mix paints for different needs, and apply them with brushes or rollers to fill in cracks or apply color on walls and other objects around a home, such as furniture pieces or doors. Implements the regular routine to moderately complex surface preparation, painting, and finishing tasks, applying a variety of methods, media, and techniques to both interior and exterior surfaces.

Title: Roofer
Description: Roofers specialize in the placement, removal and repair of various roofing materials such as asphalt, wood and plastics. Whether they lay roofing on large business buildings in commercial settings or on houses in the private sector, roofers are laborers who often work in hot, sunny conditions. As a roofer, you will use various hand and power tools. You may also clean roofs of debris. Roofers must be able to work long hours of physical labor, should work well with their hands and should have the ability to bend and climb. Being able to read blueprints and diagrams is necessary to ensure that you can follow instructions on the job.They have to sort out issues related to leakage or any damage pertaining to the roof.

Title: Packers and Movers
Description: A professional mover, you will be packing and moving customers’ household or office belongings. Moves range from just a single item to an entire home or office. Items to be moved can often weigh several hundred pounds. Moves involving stairways are very common. Packers and Movers main task is that they help you during your relocation needs. Whenever you hire a packer and mover service they assist you in packing and moving your items safely to your destination.

Title: Pest Control Technician
Description: Responsible for identifying, selecting, mixing, and applying chemical or manual solutions to eliminate pests. Identifies pest problem and appropriate solution, applies chemical or trap, and removes animals. Customer service aspects including being timely, answering questions, making recommendations, collecting payment and other various needs.    Inspect property to ascertain possible sites of pest invasion and determine treatment type required to eliminate and prevent infestation.Identify invading pests, including: rats, termites, snakes, wasps, ants, spiders, mosquitoes, or bed bugs.

Title: Mechanic
Description: A bicycle mechanic or bike mechanic is a mechanic who can perform a wide range of repairs on bicycles. Bicycle mechanics can be employed in various types of stores, ranging from large department stores to small local bike shops; cycling teams, or bicycle manufacturers.

Title: Pet Sitter
Description: Pet sitters provide daily care for pets while their owners are on vacation. They typically stay in the home of the owner, so the pets can remain on their familiar territory. Some pet sitters limit their clientele to owners of cats and dogs. Others provide care for birds, fish, small mammals, reptiles, and amphibians

Title: Coding Tutor
Description: The coding tutors help people in computer programming by teaching them how to write codes. Their duties are to assist students in the creation and development of software and help them learn how to maintain and fix code in various formats.

Title: Computer Repair Technician
Description: Computer repair technician repairs and maintains computers and servers. The technician's responsibilities may extend to include building or configuring new hardware, installing and updating software packages, and creating and maintaining computer networks.
